
According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Elderly Care Service Platform Market was valued at USD 653 million in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 1.275 billion by 2034, growing at a CAGR of 10.3% during the forecast period. The market is expanding rapidly as population aging, increasing life expectancy, rising demand for home-based elderly care, and the adoption of AI-powered digital healthcare platforms continue to reshape senior care services worldwide.
Elderly care service platforms are becoming essential digital ecosystems that connect seniors, caregivers, healthcare providers, community organizations, and government agencies through integrated applications and online services. These platforms offer comprehensive solutions including home care appointments, health monitoring, emergency response, telehealth consultations, caregiver matching, rehabilitation services, nursing support, subsidy applications, and personalized care management.
